This paper deals with the design of transmission policies in a wireless-powered communication system, which involves information theory (IT) and networking (NI) concepts. The problem is formulated as a constrained Markov decision process (MDP) problem, which involves control theory and system dynamics (SY). The Lagrangian approach is used to convert the problem into an equivalent MDP problem, which involves optimization and game theory (GT). Finally, a sub-optimal policy is proposed, which involves mathematical analysis (MA). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SY, cs.GT, and cs.MA.
